org.gradoop.flink.model.api.functions

Interface KeyFunctionWithDefaultValue<E,K>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of the object from which the grouping key is extracted.
    K - The type of the extracted key.
    All Superinterfaces:
    KeyFunction<E,K>, Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CompositeKeyFunctionWithDefaultValues, ConstantKeyFunction, LabelKeyFunction, PropertyKeyFunction

    public interface KeyFunctionWithDefaultValue<E,K>
extends KeyFunction<E,K>
    A (grouping) key function with a default value. The value will be used in some cases where the key can not be determined or when this key function is not applicable for an element.

    This key function will work exactly like a KeyFunction in most cases.
